The Shoprite Group has opened applications for all-inclusive bursaries for the 2023 academic year. The bursaries are open to high-performing students and cover tuition fees and on-campus accommodation. The group said they are catered toward harnessing skills in food science, pharmacy, chartered accounting, logistics as well as information technology, e-commerce and retail business management. You can find the full list of bursaries on offer here. Applications close by 31 August 2022. With a work-back agreement upon graduation, bursary holders are guaranteed employment and practical experience, said Shoprite Group. Bursaries are available in the following fields of study: (Note: All bursaries are for South African citizens aged 27 or younger) Read: The ‘rule of thumb’ to avoid SARS penalties when submitting your tax return